                 who="https://papyri.info/editor/users/ngonis">Submit - Entered corrections to lines 10, 22 and 23. For lin10 Gascou proposed γί(νονται) (ἄρουραι) [β] or γί(νονται) [(ἄρουραι)] β̣; BL XII 26 records only the former. The online image shows there is no need for dots or brackets, and this is the text I’ve entered. ‘Cf. J. Gascou, CE 77 (2002) 327’ is a way of obviating the problem of attribution. Something similar in lin22; Mitthof wrote that the name must be Ὧρος but did not provide a version with dots. In lin23 then BL misreports Gascou; ‘lire’ introduces a new reading (confirmed on the image), not a ‘lege’ before a regularized form. (I have not added εἰδέναι|reg|, as in my view |reg| should not be used for morphological corrections.) — One may add vac.? between lines 23 and 24 and indent lin24.</change>
